The article is a Presidential Memorandum issued by President Donald Trump on January 27, 2017. The memorandum is titled "Rebuilding the U.S. Armed Forces" and outlines the policy of the United States to pursue peace through strength and rebuild the armed forces. It directs the Secretary of Defense to conduct a 30-day readiness review and submit a report identifying actions that can be implemented to improve readiness conditions. It also calls for the development of a budget amendment for military readiness and the submission of a plan of action to achieve readiness levels before FY 2019. Additionally, the memorandum instructs the Secretary of Defense to produce a National Defense Strategy and initiate reviews on the United States nuclear posture and ballistic missile defense capabilities. The memorandum concludes with general provisions and authorizes the Secretary to publish it in the Federal Register.